In the diagram, each circle is divided into two equal areas and $O$ is the center of the larger circle. The area of the larger circle is $64\pi$. What is the total area of the shaded regions?

\begin{tikzpicture}
% Large circle
\draw (0,0) circle (2);
% Small circle with center at O (which is on the large circle's horizontal diameter)
\draw (0,0) circle (1);
% Point O label
\node at (0.2,-0.2) {$O$};
\fill (0,0) circle (1.5pt);
% Horizontal diameter of large circle
\draw (-2,0) -- (2,0);
% Shading: top half of small circle
\fill[gray!50] (0,0) arc (0:180:1) -- cycle;
% Shading: bottom half of large circle (excluding small circle)
\begin{scope}
\clip (0,0) circle (2);
\fill[gray!50] (-2,0) rectangle (2,-2);
\end{scope}
\fill[white] (0,0) arc (180:360:1) -- cycle;
\fill[gray!50] (0,0) arc (180:360:1) -- cycle;
\fill[white] (0,0) arc (0:-180:1) -- cycle;
\end{tikzpicture}
